    std::string markdownText = R"(
# Heading
## Subheading
* Item 1
* Item 2
* Item 3
[Link](https://www.example.com)
![Image](https://www.example.com/image.jpg)
```
This is a code block.
```
)";

    std::string htmlText = markdownToHtml(markdownText);
    std::cout << htmlText << std::endl;

    return 0;
}
```

This implementation uses regular expressions to replace markdown syntax with equivalent HTML tags. Note that this is a basic implementation and may not cover all markdown syntax features. For a more comprehensive solution, consider using a dedicated markdown parsing library.

